    <div class="ui main container">
        <h2 class="ui header">Help</h2>
        <h3 class="ui header" id="system-requirements">System requirements</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Browser</strong>: Chrome (>50), Firefox(>45) or Opera(>35).</li>
            <li><strong>Audio/Video devices</strong>: At least a microphone is needed to use the application, but webcam
                is not
                mandatory.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="ui header" id="sharing-screen">Sharing your screen</h3>
        <p>If you want to share your screen with other users you must use Chrome or Firefox and install the
            corresponding extension below:</p>

        <h4>Chrome</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/unnoficial-cern-vidyo-web/nlnngkdfbolcnognhapogafdlobbldop"
                   title="Download the Vidyo WebRTC Chrome extension">{{t "meeting_box.share_modal.download_chrome_extension" }}</a>
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Firefox</h4>
        <ol>
            <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/es/firefox/addon/unnoficial-cern-webrtc-sharing/"
                   title="Download the Vidyo WebRTC Firefox extension">{{t "meeting_box.share_modal.download_firefox_extension" }}</a>
            </li>
        </ol>

        <p>Once installed, you should reload the page so the application will detect the extension.</p>
        <p><img src="images/help/6-sharing-1.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>
        <p>To share, you must click the "Share screen" button and then a window with all the available shares will
            appear if you are using Chrome or a dropdown on the upper left corner of the screen if using Firefox.</p>
        <h4 class="ui header">Chrome</h4>
        <p><img src="images/help/6-sharing-chrome.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>
        <h4 class="ui header">Firefox</h4>
        <p><img src="images/help/6-sharing-firefox.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>

        <p>Once one is selected and "Share" button is clicked, the new share will appear on the participants video zone
            (lower side of the screen).</p>

        <p><img src="images/help/6-sharing-2.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>

        <p>If you want to switch between all the available shares, you can do it by selecting the one you want on the
            sharing dropdown:</p>

        <p><img src="images/help/6-sharing-3.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>

        <h3 class="ui header" id="login">Login with your account</h3>
        <p>To login with your account using the CERN Oauth2 Authentication, click the "Login" button on the CERN
            Toolbar.</p>
        <p>Then follow the steps in the window that will open.</p>
        <p>Login with your account will fill automatically the Guest name/Your name field with your CERN display
            name.</p>


        <h3 class="ui header" id="joining-meeting">Joining a meeting</h3>
        <h4 class="ui header" id="checking-system-configuration">Checking system configuration</h4>
        <p>
            <img src="images/help/1-checking-system.png" class="ui image"/>
        </p>
        <p>The first time you will access the application, It will ask you for permissions to access your microphone and
            it will check if the application environment is working.
        </p>
        <p><img src="images/help/1-2-checking-system-error.png" class="ui centered image"/>
        </p>
        <p>
            If for some reason an error occurs, you can click one of the buttons bellow to try a different application.
            The options are the following:
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Go to Vidyo Portal</strong>: If you click this button you will be redirected to CERN Vidyo
                Portal.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Use another Vidyo Client</strong>: You will be redirected to the downloads page.</li>
        </ol>
        <h4 class="ui header" id="meeting-information">Entering the meeting information</h4>
        <p><img src="images/help/2-login-form.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>
        <p>If the system check is ok, then the login screen will appear. On this screen there are 3 fields:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Room URL:</strong> You have to fill it with the Vidyo Portal URL for the room. It has the
                following format:
                <ul>
                    <li>https://vidyoportal.cern.ch/flex.html?roomdirect.html=&key=hsjT7YiPtmp7</li>
                    <li>The <strong>"Set Test Room"</strong> buttom will prefill the field with the Vidyo Cafe room URL.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Room Pin: </strong> If the room is PIN protected you can enter the password here.</li>
            <li><strong>Guest name/Your name: </strong> Enter the name you want to display in the meeting.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Once everything is set up, you can either click "Join the meeting button" or the Settings button <img
                src="images/help/2-settings-button.png" class="ui mini spaced image"/> to configure
            your devices.</p>
        <h3 class="ui header" id="configuring-meeting">Configuring a meeting</h3>
        <p><img src="images/help/3-configuration.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>
        <p>On the configuration screen you can configure the following things:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Webcam</strong>: The webcam that will be used by the application.</li>
            <li><strong>Microphone</strong>: The webcam that will be used by the application.</li>
            <li><strong>Notifications</strong>: Enable or test the browser notifications for the application. To disable
                them, you have to go to your browser settings.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="ui warning message">
            <div class="header">
                Firefox users
            </div>
            If you are using Firefox, the only available option will be "Default". You will be able to change the device
            settings on the meeting loading screen.
        </div>
        <h4 class="ui header">Loading the meeting</h4>
        <p><img src="images/help/4-loading-firefox.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>
        <p>If you are using Firefox, in this step you will need to give the application permissions to access your
            microphone and webcam.
        </p>
        <h3 class="ui header">On a meeting</h3>
        <p><img src="images/help/5-meeting.png" class="ui centered image"/></p>
        <p>Once you are on a meeting you will see 5 different zones on the screen.</p>
        <h4 class="ui header" id="participants-list">1. Participants list</h4>
        <p>The participants list will display all the participants in the meeting if you hover it.</p>
        <p>Clicking in one of the participants, a private chat with that participant will be openend.</p>

        <h4 class="ui header" id="main-toolbar">2. Main toolbar</h4>
        <p>The main toolbar will allow you to perform actions related with the meeting's behaviour.</p>

        <table class="ui celled table">
            <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>{{t "meeting_box.help_modal.enabled_icon" }}</th>
                <th>{{t "meeting_box.help_modal.disabled_icon" }}</th>
                <th>{{t "meeting_box.help_modal.description" }}</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
