                    Enables or disables the speaker. If you hover it, you can use the slider to handle the meeting's
                    volume.
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons">picture_in_picture</i>
                </td>
                <td>
                    -
                </td>
                <td>
                    Hides or shows all the small videos (the self video and the participants videos).
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons">view_compact</i>
                </td>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons">view_comfy</i>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Toggles between active speaker (default, the participant who is is talking will appear on the main
                    video) or manual speaker (the main video will be selected manually).
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons">settings</i>
                </td>
                <td>
                    -
                </td>
                <td>
                    Displays information about the meeting and also some links to give feedback and get help.
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons">screen_share</i>

                </td>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons">stop_screen_share</i>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Displays a dropdown to share the screen and select between active shares.
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <i class="material-icons red-text darken-3">call_end</i>
                </td>
                <td>
                    -
                </td>
                <td>
                    Disconnects from the meeting.
                </td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <h4 class="ui header" id="self-video">3. Self video</h4>
        <p>It will display your webcam video (what others can see). If your webcam or microphone are disabled, icons
            will appear on one of the corners.</p>
        <h4 class="ui header" id="participants-videos">4. Participants videos</h4>
        <p>Here there will be displayed the video streams from other participants (maximum number is 3 + the screen
            sharing video).</p>
        <p>If you click one of the videos, it will be switched off with the big main video.</p>
        <h4 class="ui header" id="chat-box">5. Chat box</h4>
        <p>With the chat box you will be able to send and receive public messages (from the main chat) and private
            messages (if you clicked on a user in the participants list or if other participant sends you a
            message).</p>
        <p>You can switch between all the available chats by clicking on the top left button, which displays the name of
            the current active chat.</p>
        <p>You can hide the chat box by clicking on the arrow buttom over the chat box.</p>

